               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1200" notAfter="1500"/>
                  
                  <t:ab type="history">Local tradition claims the foundation of the church in the <t:date notBefore="1200" notAfter="1300">time of King <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4327GabraMa">Gabra Masqal</t:persName>
                     </t:date>. 
                     The church must have been founded in the <t:date notAfter="1500">pre-15th century period</t:date>, and be re-established during the reign of King Yoḥannǝs IV (1872-1889). 
                     The church of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0082UMQ">ʿUra Masqal</t:placeName> (now deserted), on the top of the rock, appears to be an older institution.
                  </t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">
                     <t:figure>
                        <t:graphic url="Sites/UM.tif">
                           <t:desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</t:desc>
                        </t:graphic>
                     </t:figure>
                     The library consists of some 55 MSS. In the past, many of them are said to have been kept at <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0082UMQ">ʿUra Masqal</t:placeName>.
                     56 Mss. photographed: <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum001">UM-001</t:ref> "Homily of the Trinity"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum002">UM-002</t:ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum003">UM-003</t:ref> "Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum004">UM-004</t:ref> "Homily of the Saviour of the World"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum005">UM-005</t:ref> "Synaxarion (March)"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum006">UM-006</t:ref> "Homily of St. Mary"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum007">UM-007</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum008">UM-008</t:ref> "Vita of Cyriacus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum009">UM-009</t:ref> "Vita of Cyriacus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum010">UM-010</t:ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum011">UM-011</t:ref> "Homily of the Cross"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum012">UM-012</t:ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum013">UM-013</t:ref> "Four Gospels"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum014">UM-014</t:ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum015">UM-015</t:ref> "Synaxarion (September)"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum016">UM-016</t:ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum017">UM-017</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum018">UM-018</t:ref> "Vitae of the Martyrs"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum019">UM-019</t:ref> "The Book of the Baptismal Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESum020">UM-020</t:ref> "Vita of Tä